def: Of or pertaining to Myrmica, a genus of ants including thesmall house ant (M. molesta), and many others.
The bear's-foot (Helleborus foetidus); -- so called because theroot was used in settering, or inserting setons into the dewlaps ofcattle. Called also pegroots. Dr. Prior.
A slight withdrawal from view or knowledge. Sir W. Hamilton.
To drench; to saturate with moisture; to soak. Shak.
A large South American goatsucker (Nyctibius grandis).
Made thrice as much; threefold; tripled. Triplicate ratio(Math.), the ratio of the cubes of two quantities; thus, thetriplicate ratio of a to b is a3: b3.
Concerned in the development and formation of blood vessels andblood corpuscles; as, the vasoformative cells.
To censure or rebuke; to hold up to reprobation; to scold.[Slang]
